1. Danas sam obišao *polja* (nominative plural) sa svojim ocem. (Today I visited *fields* with my father.)
2. U *poljima* (locative plural) ima mnogo visoke trave. (There is a lot of tall grass in the *fields*.)
3. Volim da gledam kako *polje* (nominative singular) raste. (I like to watch how the *field* grows.)
4. Žetva će uskoro početi u ovim *poljima* (locative plural). (The harvest will soon begin in these *fields*.)
5. Svetlost meseca se reflektuje na *polju* (locative singular). (The moonlight is reflected on the *field*.)
6. Radnici su zasadili mnogo kukuruza u ovom *polju* (locative singular). (The workers planted a lot of corn in this *field*.)
7. Videla sam predivan prizor - *polja* (nominative plural) zlatnog žita. (I saw a beautiful sight - *fields* of golden wheat.)
8. Košenje trave je naporno, ali moramo to uraditi kako bi *polje* (nominative singular) bilo lepo. (Mowing the grass is hard work, but we have to do it to make the *field* look nice.)
9. Ispred mene se prostire veliko *polje* (nominative singular) suncokreta. (In front of me is a large *field* of sunflowers.)
10. Planiramo da posadimo više drveća oko *polja* (genitive singular). (We plan to plant more trees around the *field*.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "polja" means "fields" in English, and it can be declined in different cases, such as nominative, genitive, locative, etc. The star (*) is used to highlight the word "polja" in each sentence.